'''State Highway 16''' is a short east<U+2013>west route in [[El Paso County, Colorado|El Paso County]], south of [[Colorado Springs]].  Highway 16 constitutes the westernmost portion of a longer road known as the '''Mesa Ridge Parkway'''.

The eastern and western termini of this highway are both in the city of [[Fountain, Colorado|Fountain]].  However, part of the route passes through an [[unincorporated area]] of [[El Paso County, Colorado|El Paso County]].
==Route description==
[[Image:Fountain creek park Fountain CO.jpg|left|thumb|200px|Fountain Creek near [[Fountain, Colorado]], near SH 16]]
SH 16 begins with an interchange at [[Interstate 25 in Colorado|I-25]], which also provides access to Frontage Road.<ref name="co">{{cite web|url=http://www.mesalek.com/colo/r1-19.html#16|title=Colorado Routes 1-19|accessdate=April 1, 2010}}</ref> From here, it heads southeast, crosses [[Fountain Creek]], and intersects [[U.S. Route 85 in Colorado|US 85]]. It then becomes four lanes<ref name="co"/> and curves northward. From there, it extends east several miles eastward and ends at [[Colorado State Highway 21|SH 21]], known there as Powers Boulevard.

==History==
The route was established in 1971 from I-25 east to US 85, totaling about one mile.<ref name="co"/> It was gradually extended until 2007, when Mesa Ridge Parkway was added to the route, and the route length almost tripled.<ref name="co"/>

==Major intersections==
The entire route is located in [[El Paso County, Colorado|El Paso County]].
